metadata.title: Boeing-Stearman Model 75
aws::graph::propositions: The U.S. Army Air Forces Model 75 Kaydet had three different designations.
The three designations for the Model 75 Kaydet were PT-13, PT-17 and PT-18.
The designation of the Model 75 Kaydet depended on which type of radial engine was installed.
PT-13 was the initial production version with Lycoming R-680-B4B engine.
PT-13A was the Model A75 with R-680-7 engine.
92 PT-13A aircraft were delivered from 1937 to 1938.
255 PT-13B aircraft were delivered from 1939 to 1941.
PT-13C consisted of six PT-13Bs modified for instrument flying.
PT-13D was the Model E75 with R-680-17 engine.
PT-17 was the version with Continental R-670-5 engine.
PT-17A consisted of 136 PT-17s modified with blind-flying instrumentation.

text:
### USAAC/USAAF designations
The U.S. Army Air Forces Model 75 Kaydet had three different designations, PT-13, PT-17 and PT-18, depending on which type of radial engine was installed. 

PT-13
Initial production version with Lycoming R-680-B4B engine, 26 built in 1936
PT-13A Model A75 with R-680-7 engine, 92 delivered from 1937 to 1938.
PT-13B R-680-11 engine, 255 delivered from 1939 to 1941.
PT-13C Six PT-13Bs modified for instrument flying.
PT-13D Model E75 with R-680-17 engine, 793 delivered
PT-17
Version with Continental R-670-5 engine, 2,942 delivered.
PT-17A 136 PT-17s modified with blind-flying instrumentation.
